<html metal:use-macro="here/@@standard_macros/master">
  <head>
    <link metal:fill-slot="link" />
    <script metal:fill-slot="script" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div metal:fill-slot="content">              
      <div class="oc-headingBlock">
         <h1>Welcome to OpenPlans!</h1>
         <p class="oc-headingContext">OpenPlans aims to transform social activism by providing tools that connect people and enable them to share ideas, stay organized, and act collectively to effect change.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div id="oc-content-main">
      
      <p>Whether you are advocating for public space or working towards better schools, we hope you use OpenPlans to make your community a better place.&nbsp; Our tools help you <a style="" href="http://www.openplans.org/projects/openplans-help/create-a-new-project">create</a> or <a style="" href="http://www.openplans.org/projects/openplans-help/contribute-to-an-existing-project">contribute</a> to web sites, <a style="" href="http://www.openplans.org/projects/openplans-help/add-files-to-a-page">share files</a>, upload photos, <a style="" href="http://www.openplans.org/projects/openplans-help/create-and-manage-mailing-lists">manage mailing lists</a>, and (soon!) manage to-do lists. OpenPlans is collaborative software so most <a style="" href="http://www.openplans.org/projects/openplans-help/edit-an-existing-page">pages are editable</a>. It takes just seconds to <a style="" href="http://www.openplans.org/join_form">register</a> and, once you <a style="" href="http://www.openplans.org/login_form">log in</a>, you can <a style="" href="http://www.openplans.org/projects/openplans-help/create-a-new-project">start your own project</a> or <a style="" href="http://www.openplans.org/projects/openplans-help/contribute-to-an-existing-project">contribute to an existing one</a>.</p>
      
      <div class="oc-column-group">
          <div class="oc-widget oc-widget-feed oc-column-left">
            <h2>Newest projects</h2>
            <ul class="oc-widget-feed-list">
          <li class="oc-feed-item oc-clearAfter" tal:repeat="project view/recently_created_projects">
            <img class="oc-avatar" src="" tal:attributes="src project/image_src | nothing" />
            <h3 class="oc-feed-item-title">
                  <a href="" tal:attributes="href project/absolute_url" tal:content="nocall: project/title">Project title</a>
            </h3>
            <p class="oc-feed-item-description" tal:content="project/mission | string: project mission statement goes here">
              This is the descriptive text for a project. Apparently it doesn't quite work right yet. Is there even a field for users to fill out or entry to call from a database?
            </p>
          </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="oc-widget oc-widget-feed oc-column-right">
            <h2>Recently updated projects</h2>
            <ul class="oc-widget-feed-list">
          <li class="oc-feed-item oc-clearAfter" tal:repeat="project view/recently_updated_projects">
            <img class="oc-avatar" src="" tal:attributes="src project/image_src | nothing" />
            <h3 class="oc-feed-item-title">
                  <a href="" tal:attributes="href project/absolute_url" tal:content="nocall: project/title">Project title</a>
            </h3>
                <p class="oc-feed-item-data oc-discreetText" tal:define="nmembers python: len(project.projectMemberIds())">
                  <span tal:replace="nmembers">YY</span> member<span tal:condition="python: nmembers > 1" tal:replace="string:s" />
                </p>
                <p class="oc-feed-item-data oc-discreetText">
                  last updated <span>Jan 1937</span>
                </p>
          </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
      
          <hr class="oc-clearElement" />
      
      </div>
      
      </div><!-- content-main -->
      
      <form class="" style="display: inline; font-size: 10px;">
        <select>
            <option value="">Get started!</option>
          <optgroup label="">
            <option value="">Discover projects</option>
            <option value="">Find people</option>
            <option value="">Start a project</option> <!-- Make conditional: logged in -->
          </optgroup>
          <optgroup label="">
            <option value="">Become a member</option> <!-- Make conditional: not logged in -->
            <option value="">Edit your profile</option>  <!-- Make conditional: logged in -->
          </optgroup>
        </select>
        <input type="submit" value="Go" style="font-size: 100%;"/>
      </form>
      
      <div id="oc-content-sidebar">
      
          <div class="oc-widget oc-widget-feed">
            <h2>OpenPlans News</h2>
            <ul class="oc-widget-feed-list">
          <li class="oc-feed-item oc-clearAfter">
            <img class="oc-avatar" src="" tal:attributes="src project/image_src | nothing" />
            <h3 class="oc-feed-item-title">
              <a href="">News item</a>
            </h3>
            <p class="oc-feed-item-data oc-discreetText">
              by <a href="">username</a> on <span>Jan 1937</span>
            </p>
          </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
      
      <div class="oc-clearAfter">
        <h3>About us</h3>
        <img class="oc-image-bright" src="http://www.openplans.org/site-home/orange_logo.gif" alt="The Open Planning Project" />
        <p>OpenPlans is a production of <a href="http://topp.openplans.org/">The Open Planning Project</a>, a New York City based non-profit organization dedicated to using technology to enhance community participation. In addition to OpenPlans, we also sponsor <a href="http://www.geoserver.org/">GeoServer</a>, an open source platform for sharing geographic information, and the <a ref="http://www.nycsr.org/">New York City Streets Renaissance Campaign</a>, which advocates for lively public space in New York City.</p>
      </div>
      
      </div><!-- content-sidebar -->
    </div><!-- content-fill-slot -->
  </body>
</html>
